original: Ahrne, Gustaf Erik, bankdirektör, Falkenberg, f. 25/9/82 i Linköp. G. 12 m. Elvy Svensson, d. 29. Barn: Gustaf f. 15, kapt. v. flott., Sthlm, Sven 21, civilekon., Sthlm, Lii 23, kor-resp. — Studrex. i Linköp. 02, ge-nomg. Gbgs handiinst. 03. Anst. i Sv res Riksbank i Linköp. 04, i Skånes Ensk. Bank 04, i Halmstads Bank A-B 07, i dåv. A-B Göteborgs Hand:-bank 12, dir. f. Smålands En;sk. Bank i Halmstad siamt led. av ’styr. 17, anst. i dåv. A-B Nord. Handrbanken 25 o. led. av styr. f. kon,t. i Falkenberg 34 samt även av styr. f. kont. i Slöinge 34.
translated: Ahrne, Gustaf Erik, bank director, Falkenberg, born on September 25th, 1882 in Linköping. Married to Elvy Svensson in 1912, she passed away in 1929. Children: Gustaf, born in 1915, captain in the navy, living in Stockholm; Sven, born in 1921, economist, living in Stockholm; Lii, born in 1923, correspondent. Studied in Linköping in 1902 and completed business studies in Gothenburg in 1903. Employed by the Swedish National Bank in Linköping in 1904, and later worked for Skånes Enskilda Bank in 1904, Halmstad Bank AB in 1907, and then for the former AB Gothenburg Handelsbank in 1912. Became a director for Smålands Enskilda Bank in Halmstad and a member of the board in 1917. Employed by the former AB Nordic Handelsbanken in 1925 and a member of the board of directors for a company based in Falkenberg in 1934, as well as a member for the board of directors for a company based in Slöinge in 1934.
